        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 10:16PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1016 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Rutherfordton, or 5 miles east of Lake Lure,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rutherfordton, Lake Lure, Shingle Hollow, Green Hill, Sugar Hill,
Thermal City, and Union Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
